	  </p>
	  <p>
		<img src= "/assets/courgette.jpg" img class= "img-responsive pull-right" Hspace="10" width="240" Vspace="10">  
		You should now be beginning to see some flowers and baby courgettes on your plant. Courgette plants produce a bountiful crop, so harvest them regularly when each fruit is 15-20cm in length, and remember to keep on top of them: it only takes a couple of days and they will grow to become marrows. The flowers are also tasty, so don't throw them away when you pick your fruit - simply add them in to a stir fry instead. When picking each courgette, simple twist and pull, but be careful - the leaves and fruit have tiny hairs that can irritate your skin, so you may wish to wear gloves. You may also start to notice some white mould on the larger leaves - don't worry this can be quite common and is not harmful to you or the plant.
